sections.title: How the population has changed in Broxbourne
sections.label: Select another local authority

sections.content: In 2020, Broxbourne was the 35th largest local authority in the East of England, with a total population of 97,592. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the East of England, 2002-2020
Population density in Broxbourne
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Broxbourne was 1,897 people per square kilometre, which was more than the East of England (328), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the East of England, 2020
Median age in Broxbourne
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Broxbourne was 40 years, which was younger than the East of England (42 years), and younger than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
